snippet: Egypt has a dilemma: its politics are dominated by democrats who are not liberals and liberals who are not democrats.
abstract: Op-Ed article by international studies scholar Samer S Shehata comments on political turmoil in Egypt, where vast throngs are calling for ouster of Pres Mohamed Morsi and his Islamist government; examines what is at stake in clash between country's Islamists and secularists.
lead_paragraph: Egypt has a dilemma: its politics are dominated by democrats who are not liberals and liberals who are not democrats.
